The permissions request just grants your app permission to access location when location is available. To actually request that the location services be re-enabled (if they&#39;re turned off) you can use [`SettingsClient`](https://developers.google.com/android/reference/com/google/android/gms/location/SettingsClient) and `LocationSettingsRequest` from Google Play Services.

```kotlin
LocationServices.getClient(context)
  .checkLocationSettings(
    LocationSettingsRequest.builder()
      .addLocationRequest(
        LocationRequest.Builder(/* intervalMillis= */ 5000)
          .setPriority(Priority.PRIORITY_HIGH_ACCURACY)
          .build()
      )
  )
  .addOnCompleteListener { task -&gt;
    try {
      task.getResult(ApiException::class.java)
      // If you reach this line, settings are already enabled
    } catch (ex: ApiException)
      when (ex.statusCode) {
        LocationSettingsStatusCodes.RESOLUTION_REQUIRED -&gt;
          // Launch the settings UI
          (ex as ResolvableApiException)
            .startResolutionForResult(
              activity,
              REQUEST_CODE_LOCATION_SETTINGS,
            )
        else -&gt;       
          // Couldn&#39;t change settings
      }
    }
  }
```

